DeepSeek TuLAgent desktop UI attribution

The desktop workspace UI in this project is inspired by Reasonix Desktop:
https://github.com/esengine/DeepSeek-Reasonix

The context-window and prompt-cache telemetry model was studied from Reasonix
commit 78e9e2656ae5275cbdd29429053fdcc1cc97373c (main-v2), including its separation
of current executor context, per-request cache hit/miss, session-average cache
telemetry, and provider-calibrated local estimates. DeepSeekFathom's Python and
JavaScript implementation is independently written for this project's APIs.

The read-only capability diagnostics model also studied Reasonix's skill
winner/shadowed reporting, deterministic tool contract snapshots, prompt-cost
visibility, path redaction, and explicit unsupported-capability reporting at the
same reference commit. DeepSeekFathom's implementation remains independently
written and currently reports MCP, plugin packages, and Hooks as not integrated.

The v0.1.15 runtime work also studied Reasonix's on-demand skill bodies,
hierarchical instruction discovery, stable prompt-prefix preservation, native
tool contracts, and lightweight session-list indexing at the same reference
commit. The Python provider adapters, session format, safety limits, and desktop
rendering remain independently implemented for DeepSeekFathom.

